correctness.rationale: Major factual and conceptual mismatches with the article and several untraceable/fabricated entries. Key issues: (1) Method misclassification: The article describes pulsed PECVD with simultaneous DMZ and O2 delivery; the extraction sets aldSystem.aldMethod.method = PEALD and models ALD half-cycles, which is incorrect and inconsistent with the stated deliveryMethod. (2) Timing errors: dosingTime values are given as 2.0 ms for precursor and co-reactant; the article reports plasma exposure of 2 s (not ms) and does not provide separate precursor/co-reactant dosing steps. PurgeTime is set (0 ms) despite no purge steps in pulsed PECVD. (3) Flow-rate units wrong: article reports 15 and 80 SCCM; extraction uses QUDT unit SCM-PER-MIN (standard cubic meters per minute), which is not the same as SCCM and yields unphysical magnitudes. (4) Resistivity unit/value wrong: article gives 45–~2 Ω·cm; extraction reports 45 Ω·m (100× too large and incorrect unit). (5) Fabricated parameters: nucleationPeriod (10 cycles), numberofCycles (100), uniformity (5%), conformality aspect ratio (10), absorptionCoefficient, bandGap (3.3 eV), filmDensity (5.6 g/DeciM3), elementalConcentration (50%), deviceProperties (mobility, Vth, SS, on/off, deviceStructure), safety/filmStability/reproducibility—all not reported in the article. (6) SupercycleDesign provided though not applicable to this binary process and contrary to simultaneous delivery. (7) Some values are plausible but still untraceable: refractiveIndex 1.95 (no exact value reported), carrierDensity 1e18 m^-3 (not given). (8) Minor: purgingGas set to Ar although no purge used; pressure (400 mTorr) and plasma power (100 W) are correct. Overall the process is not schema-semantically coherent with ALD and contains numerous inaccuracies and unsupported data. Properties to correct/review: aldSystem.aldMethod.method, dosingTime/purgeTime units and meaning, flowRates units, electricalProperties.resistivity units/value, removal of fabricated parameters (nucleationPeriod, deviceProperties, bandGap, absorption, uniformity, conformality, filmDensity, elementalConcentration), and supercycleDesign.

completeness.rationale: Very poor completeness and alignment. Major issues: (1) Wrong process type: the article reports pulsed PECVD of ZnO with simultaneous DMZ+O2 and modulated plasma; the extraction labels the method as PEALD and populates ALD-specific fields (dosing/purge), contradicting the source. (2) Multiple processes omitted: the study presents films across a temperature range (25–155 °C) and also compares to PE-ALD; only a single process at 25 °C is extracted. (3) Dosing/purge times incorrect/not traceable: no purge steps are used; plasma exposure is 2 s (range 1–5 s), but the extraction records 2 ms dosing for both precursor and co-reactant and sets purge times to 0 ms—fabricated and with wrong units. (4) Thickness control inconsistent: GPC 1.35 Å/pulse at 25 °C is plausible, but numberofCycles=100 with filmThickness=100 nm is inconsistent (would require hundreds of pulses); the article does not provide a specific cycle count. (5) Flow/exposure misassigned: 15 sccm is the Ar carrier, not DMZ flow; the key reported DMZ exposure (15 mTorr·s per cycle) is missing; co-reactant O2=80 sccm is correct. (6) Saturation and nucleationPeriod values are not reported; setting saturation=false and nucleationPeriod=10 cycles is ungrounded. (7) SupercycleDesign is not applicable to this binary pulsed PECVD process. (8) Material properties largely fabricated or unit-incorrect: refractive index is shown only as a trend (no exact value 1.95 given); resistivity is reported in Ω·cm (45–~2 Ω·cm) but recorded as 45 Ω·m (unit error by ×100); carrier density, band gap (3.3 eV), absorption coefficient, uniformity (5%), conformality (AR=10), and film density are not reported; film density unit (g/dm³) and value are inconsistent and ungrounded. (9) DeviceProperties (μ_FE, V_TH, SS, on/off) are not part of this paper; they are fabricated. (10) Some correct elements (substrate Si, pressure 400 mTorr, plasma power 100 W, O2 80 sccm, amorphous at RT, roughness ~2 nm below 100 °C) are present, but overall the extraction is dominated by incorrect, missing, or non-traceable values. Properties to add/revise: correct method (pulsed PECVD, not ALD), include per-temperature processes (25–155 °C) or clearly specify the chosen condition; replace dosing/purge with plasma on/off timing; use reported DMZ exposure (mTorr·s); correct resistivity units/values; remove unreported properties (device metrics, band gap, uniformity, conformality, density, carrier density, nucleation); ensure cycles/thickness are consistent and traceable.
